ensure \"docker\" is available), or set `agents.defaults.sandbox.mode=off` to disable sandboxing.\n/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/workspace/memory//2026-03-08-weather-check.md:assistant: ⚠️ Agent failed before reply: Sandbox mode requires Docker, but the \"docker\" command was not found in PATH. Install Docker (and ensure \"docker\" is available), or set `agents.defaults.sandbox.mode=off` to disable sandboxing.\n/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/workspace/memory//2026-03-07-weather-check.md:[Fri 2026-03-06 19:19 EST] location?\n/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/workspace/memory//2026-03-07-elephant-discussion.md:**They're also ecosystem engineers.** African elephants literally reshape landscapes — knocking down trees, digging waterholes, creating pathways that dozens of other species depend on. Remove the elephants, and the whole system shifts.\n/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/workspace/memory//2026-03-07-elephant-discussion.md:**The real ones (albino elephants)** exist, mostly documented in Southeast Asia — Myanmar, Thailand, occasionally Africa. They're not actually bright pink; they're more of a pale pinkish-gray or mottled, with pinkish patches around the ears, trunk, and eyes. They're incredibly rare and often considered sacred in Thai and Burmese cultures. Sadly, their lack of pigmentation makes them more vulnerable to sunburn and eyesight issues.\n/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/workspace/memory//2026-03-07-elephant-discussion.md:Were you thinking about the real albino ones, the cultural/folklore angle, or something else entirely?"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":36,"aggregated":"/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/workspace/memory//2026-03-08-claude-usage-check.md:assistant: Here's what I found:\n/Users/aiagnet/.openclaw/workspace/memory//2026-03-08-claude-usage-check.md:assistant: Opened `claude.ai/settings/billing` — that's where you'll see your plan, renewal date, and any usage limits. There's no token/dollar counter with OAuth; it's just your subscription tier (Free / Pro / 